President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of New Hampshire due to severe storms and flooding that occurred between March 14 and March 31, 2010. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts, with funding available for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures. James N. Russo has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.